fields.description:
When I am running the INSTANCE_OPERTIONS.html test I get the following errors, also console displays  {noformat} {{totals...}} {noformat} on dashboard in places of resource counts while reloading. Movie attached.

This happens in both headless mode and while viewing on VNC.

{code}

Steps to reproduce:

1) clone https://github.com/aliceh/se34euca

2) download selenium-server-standalone.jar from http://docs.seleniumhq.org/download/

3) install VNC

4) run 
{code}
export DISPLAY=:1 && java -jar ../selenium-server-standalone-2.40.0.jar  -userExtensions <path to user-extensions.jar such as "selenium_ide/Selenium_RC_Plugins/user-extensions.js"> -htmlSuite *firefox <path to UI such as "http://10.111.101.112:8888"> <path to test suite such as "selenium_ide/KOALA/INSTANCE_OPERATIONS.html">  <path to file where report is written "report.html"> -trustAllSSLCertificates
{code}

comments.body: You can upload the movie of the test from here: https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B5vVWkNyA-UdM1doS0haRkdBcHc/edit?usp=sharing
Not sure what to make  of these error messages. [~kgill] could you take a look?

I see it around 3 minutes in.
Is it possible to see any javascript console or proxy console output?
[~alice] The total counts on the dashboard may take a while to load.  Do we have a generous delay configured for the dashboard test?

Hi [~kgill], I had timeout set to 1 minute on all tests, as far as I can tell this is not a timing issue, because the instance creation and checks all succeeded. The first error is thrown right after the key-pair is created. I will try and gather more info from logs as well as proxy output.
